The paper presents a framework for autonomous navigation of robots in unknown cluttered environments, which involves mapping, path planning, and motion planning. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The mapping component uses disparity measurements obtained from a depth sensor, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The path planning component uses a stochastic method, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The motion planning component takes into account the robot's dynamic constraints, model, and environmental uncertainty, which involves control systems (cs.SY) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.SY.
